# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# [Reserved: While called "environment variables", the file contents are static.
#  The application reads these values at startup. Changes require file edit
#  and application restart - values are not mutable at runtime.]
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Related Files (Types)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# File Variants:
#   - .env            - Default environment (gitignored)
#   - .env.example    - Template with placeholders (committed)
#   - .env.local      - Local overrides (gitignored)
#   - .env.development - Development settings (gitignored)
#   - .env.production  - Production settings (gitignored)
#   - .env.test        - Test environment (gitignored)
#
# Security:
#   - .gitignore: Must exclude .env files
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Type Behaviors
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# [Reserved: Environment files have no executable behaviors.
#  The file is declarative KEY=VALUE pairs - dotenv loaders read
#  and populate process.env or os.environ at application startup.]
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Usage/Behavior (Rails Infrastructure)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Loading Order (typical):
#   1. System environment variables (highest priority)
#   2. .env.local (local overrides)
#   3. .env.[environment] (environment-specific)
#   4. .env (base defaults, lowest priority)
#
# Syntax Rules:
#   - KEY=value (no spaces around =)
#   - Quotes optional for simple values
#   - Use quotes for values with spaces: KEY="value with spaces"
#   - Comments start with #
#   - Blank lines are ignored
#   - No variable interpolation in most loaders
#
# Security Notice:
#   MUST be in .gitignore - NEVER commit real secrets!
# =============================================================================

