# 5. Security Considerations (Security Checklist)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Before committing or deploying:
#
#   ✅ .env is in .gitignore
#   ✅ .env.example has placeholder values only
#   ✅ Real secrets are NEVER in git history
#   ✅ Production secrets use secure secrets manager
#   ✅ API keys are scoped to minimum required permissions
#   ✅ Secrets are rotated periodically
#
# If secrets were accidentally committed:
#   1. Rotate ALL exposed credentials immediately
#   2. Use git filter-branch or BFG to remove from history
#   3. Force push (coordinate with team)
#   4. Review access logs for unauthorized use
